GG ClockSaver

- Activate after 4 minutes of inactivity


Requirements:

- Linux desktop environment running on X11 (Xorg)
- Qt6 runtime libraries
- X11 Screen Saver extension library (libXss)

Tested on:
- Linux Mint
- Ubuntu X11
- Debian X11
- XFCE
- Cinnamon
- KDE Plasma X11

Not supported:
- Wayland sessions

Required packages on Debian/Ubuntu/Linux Mint:

sudo apt install libqt6core6 libqt6gui6 libqt6widgets6 libxss1

Run:

1. Copy the entire folder to /opt/.
2. Copy "GG Clock Saver" (gg-clocksaver.desktop) to your Startup (Autostart) folder.

The application is a desktop executable. By adding it to Startup, the screensaver will run in the background at all times, monitoring user inactivity and automatically activating when the system becomes idle.


-----------------------
-----------------------

If you have the C++ and Qt development libraries installed, you can compile the program manually like this:

g++ main.cpp -o gg-clocksaver $(pkg-config --cflags --libs Qt6Widgets) -lX11 -lXss

